cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use SNDR Core Engine (Genesis vLLM Patches), please cite it."
type: software
title: "SNDR Core Engine — Genesis vLLM Patches"
abstract: >-
  Runtime patch-overlay for vLLM enabling Qwen3.6 / Gemma4 inference on consumer
  NVIDIA GPUs (RTX 3090 / 4090 / 5090 / A5000): TurboQuant k8v4 KV-cache quant,
  MTP speculative decoding, hybrid Gated-DeltaNet linear attention, tool-calling,
  and 256K-class context. An in-memory overlay applied at boot — not a fork of
  vLLM. Patches retire automatically once upstream merges the underlying fix.
authors:
  - family-names: Barzov
    given-names: Aleksandr
    alias: Sandermage
repository-code: "https://github.com/Sandermage/sndr_core_engine"
url: "https://github.com/Sandermage/sndr_core_engine"
license: Apache-2.0
version: "12.0.0"
date-released: "2026-06-29"
keywords:
  - vLLM
  - LLM inference
  - consumer GPU
  - quantization
  - speculative decoding
  - KV cache
  - Qwen3.6
  - Gemma4
  - mixture of experts
  - long context
